column5: Very nice Andrew, way to go
Right On PAB!!!  Solid ski and it looks like a scenic place to fish 'em!
Beautiful fish indeed.  Do a figure 8 after every cast on every body of water.

Very nice ski gotta love them figure 8 strikes. I've heard it many places and times in different versions a musky is a musky no matter where your fishing keep at the 8's. I'm still trying to figure them out for trolling but I always cross the playner board lines.
beauty fish! Must have been a knee shaking experience
Thats a solid fish PAB! its going to be a beast at 50"!

Nice catch...  I fish clear water also... Really tough for figure 8s...  Usually my follows are 10 feet behind the lure as we as 10 feet under it... So you usually don't see them till it's too late...
Awesome fish! They dont eat the 8 on the Bay very often... good job, thick ski!
awesome looking G-Bay muskie, nice job
How you liking the new boat?
Nice musky, is that ever thick!
